<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-01T05:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-01T05:35:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00/481: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-01T14:00:00+03:25">October 1, 1938—2
                            p.m.</date><lb/>[Received October 1—12:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>103. Referring to the Department’s circular telegram September 27, 4 p.m., in
                        the event of a general European war there appears to be no reason to expect
                        immediate disturbances in Persia or new difficulties except possibly of a
                        financial or economic nature.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>